body:
It looks indeed that the format of the X-Oc-Mtime header is invalid. I've done some troubleshooting with the official Stack client and if you upload a file to your storage the header will be like the included image. The Mtime is in the format of a Unix timestamp without any nano seconds.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5831104/73777456-60e20580-4781-11ea-9c9f-8d462c9c50ac.png)
 i guess the code below should be edited but i haven't tested it yet.

`	if f.useOCMtime {
		opts.ExtraHeaders["X-OC-Mtime"] = fmt.Sprintf("%f",float64(src.ModTime(ctx).UnixNano())/1e9)
	}`
